gomodel:SYNGO_3119  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Results section: \"ArfGAP3 is present at the photoreceptor synaptic ribbon complex\"\n\n-Literal:\"To define the relation between ArfGAP3 and synaptic ribbons, we performed double immunolabelings with rabbit polyclonal antibodies against ArfGAP3 and mouse monoclonal antibodies against RIBEYE(B)-domain/CtBP2 (Fig. 9). The ArfGAP3 immunosignals largely overlapped at the photoreceptor ribbon synapse with the RIBEYE immunosignals indicating that ArfGAP3 is strongly enriched at the synaptic ribbon complex (Fig. 9A,B).(...) To further corroborate these findings, we performed SR-SIM of thin retinal sections double immunolabeled with affinity-purified rabbit polyclonal antibodies against ArfGAP3 and mouse monoclonal antibodies against RIBEYE(B)/CtBP2 (Fig. 11). Also, SR-SIM analyses demonstrated a strong enrichment of the ArfGAP3 immunosignals at the synaptic ribbons (Fig. 11).\". Experimental description: Materials and Methods section: \"IMMUNOLABELING OF 0.5-MM-THICK RETINAL RESIN SECTIONS\":\n\n-Literal: \"Epon-embedded samples of mouse and bovine retinas were prepared as previously described (Wahl et al., 2013). From the tissue blocks, 0.5-μm-thick sections were cut with a Reichert ultramicrotome. Epon was removed as described previously (Wahl et al., 2013). Afterward, sections were incubated with the respective primary and secondary antibodies as described previously (Schmitz et al., 2000; Alpadi et al., 2008; Wahl et al., 2013).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3119" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

